ttp_template:
<group name="network_mask_interface">
C {{NETWORK}}/{{MASK}} is directly connected, {{INTERFACE | ORPHRASE}}
</group>
<group name="network_mask_ad_cost_nexthop">
S {{NETWORK}}/{{MASK}} [{{AD}}/{{COST}}] via {{NEXTHOP | ORPHRASE}}
</group>
<group name="network_mask_ad_cost_nexthop_time_interface">
O {{NETWORK}}/{{MASK}} [{{AD}}/{{COST}}] via {{NEXTHOP}}, {{TIME}}, {{INTERFACE | ORPHRASE}}
</group>
cli_content:
Codes: K - kernel, C - connected, S - static, R - RIP, M - mobile, B - BGP
       D - EIGRP, EX - EIGRP external, O - OSPF, IA - OSPF inter area 
       N1 - OSPF NSSA external type 1, N2 - OSPF NSSA external type 2
       E1 - OSPF external type 1, E2 - OSPF external type 2
       i - IS-IS, L1 - IS-IS level-1, L2 - IS-IS level-2, ia - IS-IS inter area 
       * - candidate default, U - per-user static route, o - ODR
       P - periodic downloaded static route

Gateway of last resort is not set

C    192.168.1.0/24 is directly connected, Ethernet0
S    10.10.10.0/24 [1/0] via 10.10.20.2
O    10.1.1.0/24 [110/2] via 10.0.0.1, 00:00:21, FastEthernet0/1
     [110/2] via 10.0.0.2, 00:00:21, FastEthernet0/2
D EX 172.16.10.0/24 [170/3072] via 10.10.10.2, 00:00:11, Ethernet0
textfsm_template:
Value CODES (\S+)
Value NETWORK (\S+)
Value MASK (\S+)
Value AD (\d+)
Value COST (\d+)
Value NEXTHOP (\S+)
Value TIME (\S+)
Value INTERFACE (\S+)

Start
  ^\s*C\s+${NETWORK}/${MASK}\s+is directly connected, ${INTERFACE}\s*$$ -> Record
  ^\s*S\s+${NETWORK}/${MASK}\s+\[${AD}/${COST}\] via ${NEXTHOP}\s*$$ -> Record
  ^\s*O\s+${NETWORK}/${MASK}\s+\[${AD}/${COST}\] via ${NEXTHOP}, ${TIME}, ${INTERFACE}\s*$$ -> Record
  ^\s*D\s+EX\s+${NETWORK}/${MASK}\s+\[${AD}/${COST}\] via ${NEXTHOP}, ${TIME}, ${INTERFACE}\s*$$ -> Record
